To self-host an MLflow tracking server, you must use Python 3.10 or higher. Once the server is running, you can initialize the MLflow SDK in your TypeScript application using the following code:

```typescript
import * as mlflow from '@mlflow/core';

mlflow.init({
  trackingUri: 'http://localhost:5000',
  experimentId: '<experiment-id>',
});
```

To access the MLflow UI with a NodePort service, you must retrieve the assigned node port and the node IP address. You can do this by running the following commands in your terminal:

export NODE_PORT=$(kubectl get --namespace <namespace> -o jsonpath="{.spec.ports[0].nodePort}" services <mlflow-service-name>)
export NODE_IP=$(kubectl get nodes --namespace <namespace> -o jsonpath="{.items[0].status.addresses[0].address}")

Once these variables are set, you can access the UI at http://$NODE_IP:$NODE_PORT.

